        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-26T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-26T22:00:00-05:00" n="1024" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1024">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.81/2–2746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-27T10:00:00+07:00">February 27, 1946—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 28—6:53 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>376. Please inform Commerce. Reconsideration of its previous recommendation to
                    Legislative Yuan regarding “doing business” provision of articles 7 and 292 of
                    revised company law was not among matters taken up by Supreme National Defense
                    Council in its meeting on Feb 25. (Sent Washington 376 repeated Shanghai 140,
                    Feb 27, 10 a.m.) Next meeting of Council will be March 11. We are awaiting
                    Dept’s instructions and replies to Embtel 301, Feb. 15, 8 a.m. and 347, Feb. 22,
                    9 a.m. before taking further steps.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
